content: Definitely NOT a "flash"card. More of a book on each card. Also, most cards I can't see. Bigger than the screen and I can't scroll up or down to read the definition.

Definitions start with term If you start the flash cards the default method (definition first) every definition starts with the term. For example definition "A 1 year ARM is a blah blah" for the term "1 year ARM"
It doesn't provide any study materials for the price paid other than to offer you other services and products provided by the company at a much higher rate than the initial $2.99 cost.

super easy to use app that helps out, especially if new to mortgage. A lot better that just a list or an imdex. hate the box of cards they send with the book. Wish the app was included when signing up, but $3 is no biggie compared to price of course.
How can it not have any terms necessary for the exam. Cannot find "trigger term" Has less vocabulary than the big box of flash cards we got from your school. Please refund me 2.99. Thanks.
The app won't open at all

Oct 2015, unable to get card app to open. Have tried trble shtg, no luck to include un-installing app several times, no reply from app's email support. Paid $ but unable to use, the $ was debited w/no problem.

Good in the sense of getting the raw information. Why can't we flip the flashcards over at will, though? For studying purposes it would nice to be able to see the acronym or topic first, then guess the definition, instead of being restricted to seeing the definition and guessing the term. Also, a shuffle feature would be nice instead of alphabetical order. Fix this, 5 stars.
